# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Docker build CONTEXT excludes.
#
# The Dockerfile (install/docker/Dockerfile) builds everything INSIDE the image
# (`npm ci`, `dotnet restore/publish`), so the context only needs:
#   client/ (minus node_modules/.angular/dist), src/ (minus bin/obj), Ameto.slnx
#
# IMPORTANT: Docker reads .dockerignore from the CONTEXT ROOT (this file), not the
# copy at install/docker/.dockerignore — that one sits next to the Dockerfile and
# is NOT applied for `docker build -f install/docker/Dockerfile .`.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Git
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github

# Agent / tool worktrees — each is a FULL repo checkout (huge)
.claude
.kilo

# IDE / editor
.vs
.vscode
*.user
*.suo

# .NET build output (rebuilt inside the image)
**/bin/
**/obj/

# Node / Angular — `npm ci` runs inside; caches & prior outputs are not needed
**/node_modules/
client/.angular/
client/dist/

# Prebuilt SPA — the Dockerfile rebuilds it and copies it into wwwroot
src/Ameto.Server/wwwroot/

# Publish artifacts
publish/
artifacts/

# Test & tooling projects (the server image doesn't need them)
tests/
tools/

# Install scripts & docs
install/
docs/
*.md

# Runtime data — NEVER bake the local store (segments + SQLite) into the context
data/

# Misc
*.ps1
*.sh
*.nupkg
